  "plan": "1) Inspect /app tree to find scripts, docs, build system, and current outputs. 2) Read /app/docs/layout.md to understand required fields and semantics. 3) Rebuild via CMake (configure+build). 4) Run /app/scripts/run-matrix.sh to generate /app/output/solver-audit.json and inspect it for failing cases and patterns. 5) Run a failing case with run-one.sh to compare its audit JSON with the matrix slice. 6) Based on failing cases, open solver source and identify where reordered layouts break indexing/order assumptions (likely row/col permutations, CSR/CSC assembly, residual computation, convergence/dirty flags). 7) Patch solver for correct permutation handling and deterministic iteration/residual calculation; rebuild and rerun audits until all cases are ok, residual_agrees true, and reruns are byte-equivalent (or JSON-equivalent) across runs.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cd /app\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "ls -la\n",
